    "### Why This Tier Exists vs Particle Swarm Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "**Deep Reinforcement Learning Advantages:**\n",
    "- **Adaptive Learning**: Agent learns from experience and improves over time\n",
    "- **Sequential Decision Making**: Naturally handles the sequential nature of container movements\n",
    "- **Policy Generalization**: Learned policies can generalize to unseen configurations\n",
    "- **Dynamic Adaptation**: Can adapt to changing environments and constraints\n",
    "- **Experience-Based**: Improves through interaction rather than explicit optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "**Limitations of Particle Swarm Optimization (Tier 3):**\n",
    "- **Static Optimization**: Solves each problem instance independently\n",
    "- **No Learning**: Cannot leverage experience from previous problems\n",
    "- **Computational Cost**: Requires population-based search for each instance\n",
    "- **Limited Adaptability**: Cannot adapt to dynamic changes during execution\n",
    "\n",
    "### Pros and Cons vs Alternative Approaches\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pros:**\n",
    "- ✓ Learns optimal policies through experience\n",
    "- ✓ Generalizes to unseen problem instances\n",
    "- ✓ Handles sequential decision making naturally\n",
    "- ✓ Adapts to dynamic environments\n",
    "- ✓ Improves performance over time with more training\n",
    "- ✓ Can handle complex state and action spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cons:**\n",
    "- ✗ Requires extensive training data and time\n",
    "- ✗ High computational cost during training\n",
    "- ✗ Performance depends on hyperparameter tuning\n",
    "- ✗ May not converge to optimal policies\n",
    "- ✗ Difficult to interpret learned policies\n",
    "- ✗ Requires careful reward function design\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use This Tier\n",
    "\n",
    "**Use Deep Reinforcement Learning when:**\n",
    "- Many similar problem instances need to be solved\n",
    "- Sequential decision making is critical\n",
    "- Generalization to unseen configurations is valuable\n",
    "- Dynamic or changing environments are expected\n",
    "- Sufficient computational resources are available for training\n",
    "- Long-term deployment justifies training investment\n",
    "- Complex state-action relationships exist\n",
    "\n",
    "**Consider alternatives when:**\n",
    "- Single problem instance needs to be solved\n",
    "- Fast solution is required for immediate use\n",
    "- Problem instances are highly dissimilar\n",
    "- Limited training data or computational resources\n",
    "- Interpretable solutions are required\n",
    "- Optimal solution guarantees are needed\n",
    "- Simple heuristics provide adequate performance"
